content: <!--This represents the collation formula for Albertus Magnus     sermones de eucharistiae 1477 (A-135A), brackets on     number representing fact that no longer considered an incunable,     in _Catalogue of Books Printed in the Fifteenth Century Now in the     Bodleian Library_  Oxford: Oxford UP, 2005 which is 735 in the     _Gesamtkatalog der Wiegendrucke_ note that th representation below     is friendlier to the _GW_ notation than it is to the Bodleian     Catalogue notation, which would summarize the first four     gatherings as  "a - d (6.4)" where brackets represent superscript -->  <collation>  <format>folio</format>  <formula>   <gatherings>   <signatureAlphabet>23 letter</signatureAlphabet>   <gatheringRange signed="yes">    <start>a</start>    <end>a</end>    <leaves>6</leaves>   </gatheringRange>   <gatheringRange signed="yes">    <start>b</start>    <end>b</end>    <leaves>4</leaves>   </gatheringRange>   <gatheringRange signed="yes">    <start>c</start>    <end>c</end>    <leaves>6</leaves>   </gatheringRange>   <gatheringRange signed="yes">    <start>d</start>    <end>d</end>    <leaves>4</leaves>   </gatheringRange>   <gatheringRange signed="yes">    <start>e</start>    <end>e</end>    <leaves>4</leaves>   </gatheringRange>   <gatheringRange signed="yes">    <start>f</start>    <end>f</end>    <leaves>6</leaves>   </gatheringRange>   <gatheringRange signed="yes">    <start>g</start>    <end>g</end>    <leaves>4</leaves>   </gatheringRange>   </gatherings>   <totalLeaves>34</totalLeaves>  </formula> </collation>
